.TH SCKOC 1 "July 2026" "sckoc 2.3.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sckoc \- read-only MSR/HSMP hardware monitor for Intel and AMD systems
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sckoc
.RI [ mon ]
.RB [ \-\-json ]
.br
.B sckoc vcore
.br
.B sckoc uncore
.RB [ \-\-json ]
.br
.B sckoc dump
.I reg
.RI [ hi:lo ]
.br
.B sckoc uninstall
.RB [ \-y ]
.br
.B sckoc
.BR version | \-V
.br
.B sckoc
.BR help | \-h
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sckoc
is a read-only hardware monitor for Intel and AMD servers and workstations.
It reports per-socket and per-core voltage, temperature, frequency (core,
mesh, IOD and DRAM), power (RAPL, PL1/PL2, PPT), C-state residency and
platform security state.
.PP
Readings are taken from Model-Specific Registers through
.I /dev/cpu/*/msr
and, on AMD, from the Host System Management Port through
.IR /dev/hsmp .
The tool only ever reads \(em it never writes to an MSR \(em so it is safe
to use under Secure Boot and kernel lockdown (integrity mode).
.PP
Root privileges are required.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.RI [ mon ]
Print the full monitor panel once. This is the default when no argument is
given. Combine with
.BR watch (1)
for a continuously refreshing display.
With
.B \-\-json
the panel is replaced by a machine-readable JSON document (schema
sckoc\-mon\-v1) carrying per-socket and per-core essentials. Per-core
rows within 10\(deC of TjMax are flagged with an exclamation mark.
.TP
.B vcore
Print per-core (or per-rail, where a board Super I/O sensor driver is
available) core voltage. On Intel this is the VID request read from MSR
0x198 (the regulator target; load-line droop is not included), not a
measured voltage.
.TP
.B uncore
Print per-domain uncore (mesh) frequency limits in MHz. Where the
intel-uncore-frequency sysfs driver is available this includes the BIOS
boot values (initial_*_freq_khz); a mismatch against the current Min/Max
limits is flagged with an asterisk, revealing limits changed at runtime.
The MSR and TPMI fallback paths expose no boot values. Intel only.
With
.B \-\-json
a JSON document (schema sckoc\-uncore\-v1) is printed instead. When the
sysfs driver is present this command works without the
.B msr
module.
.TP
.B dump \fIreg\fR [\fIhi:lo\fR]
Read MSR
.I reg
(hexadecimal, e.g. 0x198) on every socket and print the raw value. An
optional
.I hi:lo
bit range extracts just that field.
.TP
.B uninstall \fR[\fB\-y\fR]
Remove sckoc from the system. The command detects how sckoc was installed
(script installer, rpm or deb) and removes it accordingly, including shell
completion, module autoload entries and repository configuration.
.B \-y
skips the confirmation prompt.
.TP
.BR version ", " \-V
Print the version and exit.
.TP
.BR help ", " \-h
Print a usage summary and exit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B INT
Sampling window in seconds used for frequency, power and C0 residency
measurements (default: 1).
.TP
.B DMI
Override the path to the
.BR dmidecode (8)
executable.
.TP
.B READOC
Override the path to the
.B readoc
MSR-reader helper (default: /usr/libexec/sckoc/readoc, falling back to
readoc found in PATH).
.SH REQUIREMENTS
Intel readings need the
.B msr
kernel module (the
.B uncore
command alone also works without it when the intel-uncore-frequency
sysfs driver is present). AMD temperature readings need
.BR k10temp .
AMD FCLK and PPT readings need
.I /dev/hsmp
(the
.B amd_hsmp
or
.B hsmp_acpi
module, plus HSMP enabled in BIOS). Per-rail voltage readings need a board
Super I/O sensor driver such as
.BR nct6775 .
On consumer Ryzen parts (which have no HSMP) and on kernels whose
.B k10temp
predates the CPU family, the out-of-tree
.B ryzen_smu
driver is used, when present, as a read-only fallback source for
temperature, FCLK/MCLK, PPT and rail voltages; such values are marked
.IR (smu) .
On TPMI-era Xeon processors (Granite Rapids and later) running kernels
without the
.B intel-uncore-frequency-tpmi
driver, mesh and IOD frequencies are read directly from the TPMI MMIO
region by the bundled read-only
.B tpmi-uncore
helper; such values are marked
.IR (tpmi) .
This path requires kernel lockdown to be off.
Loading these modules is left to the administrator; packaged installs
autoload
.B msr
via
.IR modules\-load.d .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/libexec/sckoc/readoc
MSR reader helper invoked by sckoc.
.TP
.I /usr/libexec/sckoc/hsmp\-msg
AMD HSMP query helper invoked by sckoc.
.TP
.I /dev/cpu/*/msr
Per-CPU MSR device nodes (msr module).
.TP
.I /dev/hsmp
AMD HSMP device node.
.TP
.I /etc/modules\-load.d/sckoc\-amd.conf
Module autoload entries created on AMD hosts by the package scriptlets.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success, non-zero on error or unknown command.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
One-shot overview:
.B sudo sckoc
.TP
Two-second sampling window:
.B sudo INT=2 sckoc
.TP
Refresh every 3 seconds:
.B sudo watch \-n 3 sckoc
.TP
Intel Vcore field on all sockets:
.B sudo sckoc dump 0x198 47:32
.TP
AMD P-state 0 definition:
.B sudo sckoc dump 0xC0010064
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dmidecode (8),
.BR modprobe (8),
.BR watch (1)
